For those who have followed this saga.....
The new pump solved the problem. Good pressures at all RPMs, runs a little
cooler, and about 10-12 pressure at idle at operating temps.

The Berg pump is MUCH superior to the junk from the flaps.

Thanks again for all the help!

Ric Jablonski
Roan Mountain, TN

----- Original Message -----
From: "doc ric" <docric(-at-)preferred.com>
To: <type2(-at-)type2.com>; <vintagebus(-at-)type2.com>
Sent: Wednesday, January 02, 2002 7:59 PM
Subject: Re: [VB] Re: Oil light flickers on new rebuild. UPDATE


> History: New rebuilt 1600 SP doghouse engine, DR bored case.
> Symptom: Poor oil pressure at idle once hot.
>
> I think I have found the problem. I removed the NEW oil pump today to
check
> it and found three things.
>
> 1) The backlash was excessive. The Wilson book says there should be no
> audible clicking between the gears when wiggled holding one gear
stationary.
> There was way too much motion. (crappy manufacture) I dug out the old oil
> pump and checked, and it is much better with over 100,000 miles of use. I
> wish I had saved the box to give you guys a heads up on the brand name.
>
> 2) The shaft for the driven gear should be slightly recessed. On this one,
> there was actually a outward portion of metal remaining that was holding
the
> cover plate away from the housing. (crappy manufacture).
>
> 3) The gears measured 21mm! Two idiots involved: The flaps guy that sold
me
> the wrong part and the builder (me) who did not check. :-(
>
> I ordered a standard 26mm pump from Clyde Berg today and really think this
> will solve the problem. Fingers crossed. Thanks for all the help and
input.
>
> Ric Jablonski
> Roan Mountain, TN
>
>

